19#include "ODRowReader.h"
20
21#include <cassert>
22#include <string>
23#include <array>
24#include <vector>
25
26namespace ZXing {
27
28class DecodeHints;
29enum class BarcodeFormat;
30enum class DecodeStatus;
31
32namespace OneD {
33
34/**
35* <p>Encapsulates functionality and implementation that is common to UPC and EAN families
36* of one-dimensional barcodes.</p>
37*
38* @author dswitkin@google.com (Daniel Switkin)
39* @author Sean Owen
40* @author alasdair@google.com (Alasdair Mackintosh)
41*/
42class UPCEANReader : public RowReader
43{
44public:
45 Result decodeRow(int rowNumber, const BitArray& row, std::unique_ptr<DecodingState>& state) const override;
46
47 /**
48 * <p>Like {@link #decodeRow(int, BitArray, java.util.Map)}, but
49 * allows caller to inform method about where the UPC/EAN start pattern is
50 * found. This allows this to be computed once and reused across many implementations.</p>
51 *
52 * @param rowNumber row index into the image
53 * @param row encoding of the row of the barcode image
54 * @param startGuardRange start/end column where the opening start pattern was found
55 * @param hints optional hints that influence decoding
56 * @return {@link Result} encapsulating the result of decoding a barcode in the row
57 * @throws NotFoundException if no potential barcode is found
58 * @throws ChecksumException if a potential barcode is found but does not pass its checksum
59 * @throws FormatException if a potential barcode is found but format is invalid
60 */
61 virtual Result decodeRow(int rowNumber, const BitArray& row, BitArray::Range startGuard) const;
62
63 using Digit = std::array<int, 4>;
64
65protected:
66 // These two values are critical for determining how permissive the decoding will be.
67 // We've arrived at these values through a lot of trial and error. Setting them any higher
68 // lets false positives creep in quickly.
69 static constexpr float MAX_AVG_VARIANCE = 0.48f;
70 static constexpr float MAX_INDIVIDUAL_VARIANCE = 0.7f;
71
72 explicit UPCEANReader(const DecodeHints& hints);
73
74 /**
75 * Get the format of this decoder.
76 */
77 virtual BarcodeFormat expectedFormat() const = 0;
78
79 /**
80 * Subclasses override this to decode the portion of a barcode between the start
81 * and end guard patterns.
82 *
83 * @param row row of black/white values to search
84 * @param rowOffset on input, end offset of start guard pattern, and on output: horizontal offset of first pixel after the "middle" that was decoded
85 * @param resultString {@link StringBuilder} to append decoded chars to
86 * @throws NotFoundException if decoding could not complete successfully
87 */
88 virtual BitArray::Range decodeMiddle(const BitArray& row, BitArray::Iterator begin, std::string& resultString) const = 0;
89
90 /**
91 * @param s string of digits to check
92 * @return {@link #checkStandardUPCEANChecksum(CharSequence)}
93 * @throws FormatException if the string does not contain only digits
94 */
95 virtual bool checkChecksum(const std::string& s) const;
96
97
98 virtual BitArray::Range decodeEnd(const BitArray& row, BitArray::Iterator begin) const;
99
100public:
101 static BitArray::Range FindStartGuardPattern(const BitArray& row);
102
103 /**
104 * Attempts to read and decode a single UPC/EAN-encoded digit.
105 *
106 * @param counters the counts of runs of observed black/white/black/... values
107 * @param patterns the set of patterns to use to decode -- sometimes different encodings
108 * for the digits 0-9 are used, and this indicates the encodings for 0 to 9 that should
109 * be used
110 * @return index best matching pattern, -1 if counters could not be matched
111 * @throws NotFoundException if digit cannot be decoded
112 */
113 template <size_t N>
114 static int DecodeDigit(BitArray::Range* next, const std::array<Digit, N>& patterns, std::string* resultString) {
115 assert(next && resultString);
116
117 Digit counters = {};
118 auto range = RowReader::RecordPattern(next->begin, next->end, counters);
119 if (!range)
120 return -1;
121 next->begin = range.end;
122
123 int bestMatch = RowReader::DecodeDigit(counters, patterns, MAX_AVG_VARIANCE, MAX_INDIVIDUAL_VARIANCE, false);
124 if (bestMatch != -1)
125 resultString->push_back((char)('0' + bestMatch % 10));
126
127 return bestMatch;
128 }
129
130 /**
131 * Similar to DecodeDigit. Detects a single guard pattern instead of a digit.
132 * */
133 template <size_t N>
134 static bool ReadGuardPattern(BitArray::Range* next, const std::array<int, N>& pattern) {
135 assert(next);
136
137 std::array<int, N> counters = {};
138 auto range = RowReader::RecordPattern(next->begin, next->end, counters);
139 if (!range || RowReader::PatternMatchVariance(counters, pattern, MAX_INDIVIDUAL_VARIANCE) >= MAX_AVG_VARIANCE)
140 return false;
141
142 next->begin = range.end;
143 return true;
144 }
145private:
146 std::vector<int> _allowedExtensions;
147};
148
149} // OneD
150} // ZXing
